.SH "NAME"
pom_remove_plugin \- remove Maven plugin invocation from POM file
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fB%pom_remove_plugin\fR [groupId]:[artifactId] [POM\-location]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
This macro patches specified POM file not ta contain invocationz of given Maven plugin\&.
.sp
groupId n' artifactId is identifierz of Maven crew n' artifact of tha plugin which invocation is ta be removed\&. If they is ommited then all identifiers is matched\&.
.sp
POM location can be either a gangbangin' full path ta tha POM file, or a path ta tha directory containin \fBpom\&.xml\fR\&. If POM location aint given then \fBpom\&.xml\fR from current hustlin directory is used\&.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
\fB%pom_remove_plugin maven\-shade\-plugin\fR \- dis call removes invocation of Maven Shade Plugin from POM up in current hustlin directory\&.
